## Architecture & Auth Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant React as React Frontend :5173
    participant Express as Express Backend :3000
    participant MongoDB

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- REGISTER FLOW ---
    User->>React: Fills register form
    React->>Express: POST /api/auth/register {username, email, password}
    Express->>Express: Validate inputs
    Express->>Express: Hash password (bcrypt)
    Express->>MongoDB: Save user document
    Express->>Express: Sign JWT token
    Express->>React: Set cookie "token" + return user JSON
    React->>React: setUser(data.user) → navigate to "/"

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- LOGIN FLOW ---
    User->>React: Fills login form
    React->>Express: POST /api/auth/login {email, password}
    Express->>MongoDB: Find user by email
    Express->>Express: Compare password (bcrypt)
    Express->>Express: Sign JWT token
    Express->>React: Set cookie "token" + return user JSON
    React->>React: setUser(data.user) → navigate to "/"

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- AUTH CHECK (on page load) ---
    React->>Express: GET /api/auth/get-me (cookie sent automatically)
    Express->>Express: authMiddleware: verify JWT, check blacklist
    Express->>MongoDB: Find user by decoded ID
    Express->>React: Return user JSON
    React->>React: setUser(data.user), setLoading(false)

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- LOGOUT FLOW ---
    User->>React: Clicks Logout
    React->>Express: GET /api/auth/logout (cookie sent)
    Express->>MongoDB: Add token to blacklist collection
    Express->>React: Clear cookie + success message
    React->>React: setUser(null) → redirected to /login
```

