## Role of Every Folder & File

### Backend

| File / Folder | Role |
|---|---|
| **`.env`** | Stores secret values: `MONGO_URI` (MongoDB connection string) and `JWT_SECRET` (key to sign/verify tokens). Never commit this to git. |
| **`server.js`** | The **entry point**. Loads `.env` vars, connects to MongoDB, then starts Express on port 3000. |
| **`src/app.js`** | Creates the Express app instance. Registers global middleware: `cors` (allows frontend at :5173), `express.json()` (parses JSON bodies), `cookie-parser` (reads cookies). Mounts the auth router at `/api/auth`. |
| **`src/config/database.js`** | Exports `connectToDB()` — connects to MongoDB Atlas using `mongoose.connect()` with the URI from `.env`. |
| **`src/models/user.model.js`** | Defines the **User** Mongoose schema with fields: `username` (unique), `email` (unique), `password` (hashed). Maps to the `users` collection. |
| **`src/models/blacklist.model.js`** | Defines the **BlacklistToken** schema. When a user logs out, their JWT is stored here so it can't be reused. Has `timestamps: true` for auto `createdAt`. |
| **`src/controllers/auth.controller.js`** | Contains 4 controller functions: **register** (validate → check duplicates → hash password → create user → sign JWT → set cookie), **login** (find user → compare password → sign JWT → set cookie), **logout** (blacklist token → clear cookie), **getMe** (find user by `req.user.id` → return user data). |
| **`src/middlewares/auth.middleware.js`** | The `authUser` middleware. Reads the JWT from `req.cookies.token`, checks if it's blacklisted, verifies it with `jwt.verify()`, then attaches `req.user = decoded` so controllers can access user info. Used on protected routes like `/get-me`. |
| **`src/routes/auth.routes.js`** | Defines all auth endpoints using Express Router: `POST /register`, `POST /login`, `GET /logout`, `GET /get-me` (protected with `authUser` middleware). |

### Frontend

| File / Folder | Role |
|---|---|
| **`index.html`** | The single HTML page. Has a `<div id="root">` where React mounts, and loads `main.jsx` as a module script. |
| **`src/main.jsx`** | The React entry point. Wraps the `<App />` component inside `<AuthProvider>` (so every component can access auth state) and `<StrictMode>`. |
| **`src/App.jsx`** | Simply renders `<RouterProvider>` with the router config — this enables client-side routing. |
| **`src/app.routes.jsx`** | Defines 3 routes using `createBrowserRouter`: `/login` → Login page, `/register` → Register page, `/` → Home page wrapped in `<Protected>`. |
| **`src/pages/Home.jsx`** | The main authenticated page. Uses `useAuth()` to get the current user and a logout button. |
| **`src/features/auth/auth.context.jsx`** | Creates a React Context with `user`, `setUser`, `loading`, `setLoading` state. The `AuthProvider` component wraps the entire app so any child can consume this state. |
| **`src/features/auth/hooks/useAuth.js`** | The core custom hook. Provides `handleLogin`, `handleRegister`, `handleLogout` functions. On mount, calls `getMe()` to auto-detect if the user is already logged in (cookie still valid). |
| **`src/features/auth/services/auth.api.js`** | Creates an Axios instance with `baseURL: http://localhost:3000` and `withCredentials: true` (sends cookies). Exports 4 functions: `register()`, `login()`, `logout()`, `getMe()` — each calls the corresponding backend endpoint. |
