## Architecture — Interview AI Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant React as React Frontend :5173
    participant Express as Express Backend :3000
    participant Gemini as Gemini AI API
    participant MongoDB

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- GENERATE INTERVIEW REPORT ---
    User->>React: Fills job description + uploads resume
    React->>Express: POST /api/interview/ (FormData: resume, jobDescription, selfDescription)
    Express->>Express: authUser middleware: verify JWT
    Express->>Express: multer: parse resume file into memory buffer
    Express->>Express: pdf-parse: extract text from PDF buffer
    Express->>Gemini: generateContent() with structured schema
    Gemini->>Express: JSON response (matchScore, questions, skillGaps, plan, title)
    Express->>MongoDB: interviewReportModel.create({...aiResponse, user})
    Express->>React: 201 JSON { interviewReport }
    React->>React: navigate("/interview/:id")

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- VIEW INTERVIEW REPORT ---
    User->>React: Visits /interview/:interviewId
    React->>Express: GET /api/interview/report/:interviewId
    Express->>MongoDB: findOne({ _id, user })
    Express->>React: 200 JSON { interviewReport }
    React->>React: Render 3-column report UI

    Note over User,MongoDB: --- DOWNLOAD AI RESUME PDF ---
    User->>React: Clicks "Download Resume"
    React->>Express: POST /api/interview/resume/pdf/:reportId
    Express->>MongoDB: findById(reportId) → get resume + job description
    Express->>Gemini: Generate tailored resume as HTML
    Express->>Express: Puppeteer: convert HTML → PDF buffer
    Express->>React: PDF file (application/pdf)
    React->>React: Trigger browser download
```

