## API Endpoints Reference

### Auth Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Body | Description |
|--------|----------|------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/register` | Public | `{ username, email, password }` | Creates new user, sets JWT cookie |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Public | `{ email, password }` | Validates credentials, sets JWT cookie |
| `GET` | `/api/auth/logout` | Public | — | Blacklists token, clears cookie |
| `GET` | `/api/auth/get-me` | **Private** | — | Returns current user from JWT |

### Interview Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Body | Description |
|--------|----------|------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/interview/` | **Private** | FormData: `resume` (file), `jobDescription`, `selfDescription` | Parses resume PDF, calls Gemini AI, saves report to DB |
| `GET` | `/api/interview/` | **Private** | — | Returns all interview reports for logged-in user (lightweight) |
| `GET` | `/api/interview/report/:interviewId` | **Private** | — | Returns full interview report by ID |
| `POST` | `/api/interview/resume/pdf/:interviewReportId` | **Private** | — | Generates a tailored resume PDF using AI + Puppeteer |

---

> [!NOTE]
> The `interviewId` used in URLs is the MongoDB auto-generated `_id` field. It is created when the report is saved to the database and passed to the frontend for navigation.



